<node id="&quot;PREMIUMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"AMOUNT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Payments required to maintain the insurance policy, due when due. They are fixed for each 20-year term and guaranteed not to increase."&lt;SEP&gt;"Payments required under the insurance policy, which will not be waived if due more than 12 months before notice of total disability."&lt;SEP&gt;"Premiums are not paid under certain conditions, including fraudulent claims or upon the insured person reaching their 80th birthday."&lt;SEP&gt;"Premiums are the payments required to maintain the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The amount paid for insurance."&lt;SEP&gt;"The cost of permanent life insurance, which depends on coverage type and amount."&lt;SEP&gt;"The payments required to maintain the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The periodic payments required to maintain the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Unearned premiums are refundable if coverage is canceled and no claims are pending."</data>
